 provides important insights and recommendations regarding the organisation, co-ordination and regulation of the future mixed economy of visible security patrols. Plural policing will be of special interest to academics, researchers, policy makers, police and security managers and students of criminology and policing, as well as all those interested in community safety and the changing face of modern policing.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Criminology.2bisacsh1 aBlackburn, Sarah, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aLister, Stuart, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-1995z978311119621340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447366805423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447366805/original  a978-3-11-119621-3  Bristol University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-1995c1995d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles